    <h3>Add a comment about MVC below:</h3>
    <ul>
        <% starts.forEach( el => { %>
            <li class='startItem' data-id='<%=el._id%>'><!--  data-id property, and we can plug anything we want into it. we can change the name to whatever we want ex data-pony. el is the element, el represnts a document. a parameter that will be holding our document or object each time it runs. our objects are coming from our collections.  <%=el._id%> _id will gives the id from our documents it self.--> 
                <span ><%= el.start %></span>
                <span class='del delete-emoji'> 💣 </span>
